				posted 2004-11-16 13:38&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;
				<A href="edit.php?board=player&id=12538"><IMG alt="Edit/Delete Message" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/edit.gif" border=0></A> 
			    <A href="reply.php?board=player&id=12529"><IMG alt="Reply w/Quote" src="http://www.archspace.org/image/forum/quote.gif" border=0></A>
			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Well said, GDukin, actually. I very much agree with several of your points.<br />
<br />
The player base is filled with assholes, and lowbie AS is hell, put simply. Players die constantly. Such should not be the case.<br />
<br />
The manual, however, is actaully quite good though. What it does not go over is strategies and such that vary quite a bit player to player. The thing that keeps the vets on top generally is their experiance, knowledge, activity, and coordination with the other players in their council. Honestly though, as Dr.Jekyl pointed out, it's really not much fun to be the one on top. Sure, you can mindlessly kill the empire. That's sure fun.<br />
<br />
The first player to HBH means very little actually, or alot of players would play Xesperados and Tecanoid. There is actually more strategy than you believe too. Simply having more doomstars doesn't mean you will win a battle. Hit a well known &quot;vet&quot; at 2/3s your size. Generally you will take a good amount of damage IF you win. First to top, especially with the new rules, doesn't mean you will keep the top spot. Naru fell, did she not? Dark Empire fell, did they not? And others fell as well. AS is complex, as you say. It is more complex than the majority of it's players realize as well. I've slaughtered people double my power on numerous occasions. I've won battles or done exceedingly well in battles that most players would consider impossible to win. People underestimate what you are capable of in AS, and seldom experiment.<br />
<br />
I do think that AS needs to be much friendlier towards new players though. atm, yeah, I agree, it's terrible. It's horrendous for players starting mid-set especially. They get raped. Constantly. I discovered last set that most players don't even have full tech at week 4.<br />
<br />
People hitting people half their power for commander experiance is just gay. For planets, I can understand, but for experiance is just lame. The honor system was nerfed a bit too much imho. I have yet to suffer anything significantly impeding or obnoxious due to my generally 0 honor level.<br />
<br />
The devs are trying to work on ways to help with these problems. 'course, it doesn't help that many of the changes they propose are violently fought by many players (10 min turns). :p I think we should give 10 min turns a shot next set. It doesn't make huge differences overall, though, realistically. You can still lose all your fleets instantaniously, and your planets shortly afterwards. The same players that do well in 5 min turns still do just as well in 10 min turns. It's just more convienant for the less active players.<br />
<br />
Anyway, I'm done for now. :p<br />
<br />
AS may have problems, but it's fun, and I keep coming back to it regardless. I wonder if I'll ever be free of it's grasp by my own will.			   <P align=right></P>
