			  	I got to agree with GDukin a bit here (I have been in the top 25) not sure if making the game more complex would help though. Complex games annoy me- there's always the &quot;how the hell did that happen?!&quot; factor.<br />
<br />
I just had a member of my council quit totally basically because of the same issues... the whole HBH Doom thing was what kept us down for most of the game, and just as we were starting to get the hang of it... well, we got bombed back into the stoneage by someone bigger. And how did we get into their range? Bombing someone else without HBH dooms back into the aforementioned age. I have never seen a fair, evenly matched fight in this game, throughout its incarnations- you either get totally destroyed in an hour or you're destroying someone totally in an hour.<br />
<br />
I've led councils in the top ten, and as I said been in the top 25, and it does come down to HBH Dooms, and thats it. And also, I am fed up with some powerful tool who wants to give his commanders more exp wiping out my entire defense via blockading. Either take blockading out, or make it so their fleets actually have to stay to blockade, making it an actually risky endevour (ie- the blockader will be reducing his defenses while his ships are blockading for a day or so).<br />
<br />
Ans while I'm at it, what the hell is the point of boosts to research from the techs you get last??? (eg- Human Ending Mk1 and University of Past, Present, and Future) It's a waste. Give these projects- or at least something else that gives research boost and take it off them- earlier!			   <P align=right></P>
