			  	yeah good points!<br />
<br />
WAKE UP GUYS, AS is dying more or less.<br />
<br />
How many active players left, 200-300 ?<br />
<br />
The game is complex for starters, may be too much I dunno. The guide is supposed to help with that, but I didn't see it improved things enough yet.<br />
<br />
So, solutions:<br />
<br />
1. I hate to say, but AS needs a new server or rather new admin, I don't see Mindwarper really significantly cares about AS. He did a great job reviving AS but it's time to move on.<br />
<br />
2. Either increase tick time (8 or 10) next set and/or increase the research time, so we will hopefully see more early/mid tech battles. <br />
<br />
3. Balance. I can't say it often enough. A group of 10-15 hardcore gamers can easily rule the game once they got the top position (esp. first 48 hours) and nobody is able to catch up even if like 100 players ally up and chase them.<br />
Various reasons for that, first attackin with 2x time more power. You can set up a power border virtually, honour was supposed to balance that out a bit, but it didnt work.<br />
Also limiting council hopping didn't solve this issue and many other attempts.<br />
<br />
A) Introduce weapon travel time, it will hopefully      prevent the current situation where attackers can win minor to 0 losses all the time.<br />
It will hopefully enable more &quot;suicide runs&quot; which  were gone without commie milking.<br />
<br />
B) More difficult ideas, like Nighty's cluster  war suggestion or trying out a random round, i.e you can only jump council one time in the whole round.<br />
<br />
I also have a bunch of ideas how to help new players and advertise for new players but that's another topic.<br />
<br />
Flame away ;)<br />
<br />
P.S. the community is actually quite friendly, i have seen much worse!			   <P align=right></P>
