			  	hmmm.. true.. I'll try to use ratios to better explain my idea...<br />
<br />
doom: <br />
normal strength, yet fires at a rate of 1:1, and accuracy of 80%, average armour strength.<br />
<br />
shining star (for lack of better name atm): <br />
reduced by 10% strength, yet fires at rate of 3:1, with accuracy of 65%, 5% higher armour strength.<br />
<br />
Illusionary: <br />
average strength, rate of fire is 1:1, accuracy is 80%, armour is reduced by 15%, yet creates illusions that increase the chance of the enemy fleet fleeing by 30%.<br />
<br />
<br />
This kind of pattern could be used for all ship types, so that there are at least 3 variants of each level. 			   <P align=right></P>
