			  	Oh man... yeah i see there IS a serious problem... when people are asking to implement evasion something is sad :(. I was going to make a guide but before i finished a edead's guide came out and i thought that was fine, so I abanded mine, but now i see there are some really serious problems going on :( I might have to restart making it perhaps or someone else should. <br />
<br />
First of all, there IS evasion in the game dammit. Its been implemented since the game started. There are many factors that decide it, they each make small contribution but together they make a noted and proven impact. What you guys are confused about i think is Defence rate vs Damage Resistance since both of them are abbreviated as DR. Basically what you can do to make your ship more evasive is increase mobility, computer or armor Defence Rate  (ECM jammer, Enginnering Specialist) These factors can cause the HBH to miss and do no damage to you. However DB is hurt the most by this cause of inherntly low attack rate it already has.<br />
<br />
I thought these things were explained in the guide? Save for mobility of course.<br />
<br />
As for anyone saying that Pure HBH with uber detection is cheap and overpowered and that it destroys all strategy let me tell you this. I was able to attack someone using this strategy, they had 20 HBH fleets with high detection commies + 2 allied DB fleets. All the enemy HBH fleets fired first (and I do mean all) and yet I was still able to win the battle with a loss of 400 dooms, because the other player didn't even bother to have a proper balanced fleet, just went HBH crazy. There IS a lot of strategy inside the game, but you have to find it out for your self and learn it, and stop complaining about it, the lack of strategy is due to players not the game.<br />
<br />
Anyway yeah this game is quite complex for a noob to learn in one set though and master it unless he starts in an already developed council... making random councils idea would be fun, or perhaps just doing what MMORPGs are doing for massive PvP, divide things into realms/factions so that when you start you are already part of a team. People tend to help you better when you are part of the team, but honestly to discuss all strategy that this game has takes a lot of time.... and a lot of effort to learn too.<br />
<br />
But yeah those ideas are very radical though, so i dunno. Speed is the natural progression to evolve the game from here on out though. As suggestion forum suggests, Im all for speed :).<br />
<br />
As soon as DT codes it that is! 			   <P align=right></P>
