			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Yes DR which is influenced by mobility, ship size, computer, armor, devices etc. IS evasion. Ships avoid whole missiles and thus avoid taking damage. But if 40 missiles are fired, you are not supposed to evade 40 of them... you avoid some % thus you take less damage.<br />
<br />
Indeed the game is more complex than most people think. The original poster mentioned that it's all about building the biggest ships with HBH which is totally untrue. It is exactly the opposite, the key to early victory, the one that ensured the koreans and TE domination is actually using small ships. I assure you that I will beat the hell out of your 1 million PP worth of cruisers using 1 million PP worth of frigates. Moreover, pure HBH is stupid, unless you dominate and always have power advantage. <br />
<br />
Some adjustments has been already made to end-game weapons (PSL, OOD) to make them more competetive. Same goes for races (lots of Buckaneer love). But that's hardly important for the ultimate survival of the game.<br />
<br />
IMHO, AS would automatically fix itself if it had larger player base. Larger than any time this year.<br />
<br />
I think DOABLE things that are needed to attract new players are: <br />
<br />
- new forum. who cares if vets like being oldschool if it looks like 80-ties crap and scares off new people. come on, when you enter AS you have the impression than nothing changed for 5 years. and people outside laugh on AS for being a buggy korean game. Even if it stopped being so buggy, it has to look more decent to speak for itself.<br />
<br />
- new newbie guide (not advanced guide like the one I wrote, but updated one explaining the very basics)<br />
<br />
- better administration (news/reset annoucements on the main page but also on several gaming sites. every browser based game annouces resets on mpogd.com, but not AS. <br />
<br />
Next reset HAS to be annouced on AS page and mpogd.com and it HAS to be done a week before launch. <br />
<br />
Moreover, slower research, and... siege cooldown. YES. As much as many of you hate it, this is excellent measure to reduce the lethality of AS by great amount. Be it 5 mins attack/defense cooldown if you insisnt on 5 min. turns. Don't blame just the vets for being assholes. The whole game is lethal, some say it's even worse in mid and low councils than on the top.<br />
