			  	Hmm I would like to point out something that is not being addressed. If we are to add the cooldown only the people that have free time can benifit. Once again not everyone has the time to stay in the game and keep sieging, If we are going to add a cooldown, would it should be at least 1 attack/3 minutes or 2 attacks/for a turn of 8 minutes whichever is easier to implement. A lot of people don't have the time to login and play and it won't change the fact that you can still get killed overnight, however, now it will take forever a lot longer for you to rebuild. Granted there are good sides to cooldown, but what about the fact that redjack becomes unkillable right now? It would take around 4-5 days to take him down under the new rules, assuming no resistance. Another solution can be perhaps the cooldown should only start applying after the player is down to 20th-30th planets? Newbies don't generally get more then that anyway, but this would most definately screw things up at higher strengths, it fortifies the top.  So before major major problems arise in next set I urge to look at it once again, and think of these side effects. Not necessarily mine, but perhaps something else...			   <P align=right></P>
