			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Shadowman, you make a good point about Redjack being &quot;unkillable&quot;. However, that is only if the siege cooldown time was implemented now. If everyone were to be subjected to the cooldown time at the beginning of the set, it would be difficult to acquire as many planets as Redjack has now. <br />
<br />
Players managed with the siege cooldown time during Mari, why not now?<br />
<br />
I know that some players found that only being able to take one planet total from their target per turn (and hence others not being able to siege for a planet) was irritating. <br />
<br />
So my suggestion is: <br />
one planet per attacker per turn from the same target.<br />
<br />
This would help balance the fact that killing someone like Redjack (with over 1k planets) will not take as long. <br />
